  "descriptions": [
    {
      "text": "アーケードゲームの移植版です。アイデアは一見シンプルですが、障害物にぶつからず、コースから外れないようにマーブルを導くことが求められます。ゲームはアイソメトリック視点で表示されるため、ボールが進むべき方向に集中するのが難しくなります。狭い通路を進み、敵を避ける必要があります。2人プレイヤーモードでは、プレイヤー同士がゴールを目指して競い合うことができ、そうでなければ時間との勝負になります。\n\n日本でリリースされたバージョンには英語のテキストが含まれ、トラックボールのサポートや、より多くの難易度レベル、アーケードオリジナルに近い音楽が追加されています。",
      "lang": "ja",
      "source": "romu"
    },
    {
      "text": "Marble Madness is an isometric platform game in which the player manipulates an onscreen marble from a third-person perspective. The player controls the marble's movements with a trackball, though most home versions use game controllers with directional pads. The aim of the game is for the player to complete six maze-like, isometric race courses before a set amount of time expires. When a player completes a race, the remaining time is added to the next race's allotted time. The game also allows two players to compete against each other.\n\nCourses are populated with various objects and enemies designed to obstruct the player. As the game progresses, the courses become increasingly difficult and introduce more enemies and obstacles. Each course has a distinct visual theme. For example, the first race, titled \"Practice\", is a simple course that is much shorter than the others, while the fifth race, named \"Silly\", features polka-dot patterns and is oriented in a direction opposite from the other courses",
      "lang": "en",
      "source": "igdb"
    },
